	* `i` is the index of the first element in the subset.
	* `j` is the index of the last element in the subset.
	* `k` is the sum of the elements in the subset.
2. The base case is when `i > j`, in which case the maximum sum is 0.
3. If `i = j`, then the maximum sum is the value of the element at index `i`.
4. For `i < j`, we can consider two cases:
	* Including the element at index `j` in the subset: `maxSum(i, j - 1, k + arr[j])`
	* Excluding the element at index `j` from the subset: `maxSum(i, j - 1, k)`
5. The maximum sum is the maximum of these two cases.

